    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>119700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <div type="textpart" n="a"><ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> καὶ <orig>κ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab></div>
                <div type="textpart" n="b"><ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ν</orig> <space extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab></div>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>It is not quite clear whether this fragment belongs to a shallow basin or to a deeper bowl.</p>
	       <p>The isolated final letter of b) may form the end of the same text as a), which would be too long to be written on the rim only.
	       Alternatively, it might belong to a different text.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
